name: Harriet Tubman
description: The amazing Harriet 'Moses' Tubman was born into slavery in 1822. She escaped and went on to rescue 70 more people through the Underground Railroad. Harriet fought in the American Civil War and was the first woman to lead an armed expedition in the conflict- freeing more than 700 enslaved people! Later in life she was an activist in the Women's Suffrage Movement.
